  "data_flow": {
    "description": "End-to-end flow from disk to /api/admin/settings response",
    "steps": [
      "1. loadConfiguration() reads conf/defaults.ini via ini.Load() → *ini.File with all default values",
      "2. applyCommandLineDefaultProperties() overlays 'default.*' CLI args onto the defaults layer",
      "3. loadSpecifiedConfigFile() merges conf/custom.ini (or --config path) into the same *ini.File, overwriting defaults",
      "4. applyEnvVariableOverrides() iterates all sections/keys, calls EnvKey() to form GF_<SECTION>_<KEY>, calls os.Getenv(), and calls key.SetValue() if non-empty",
      "5. applyCommandLineProperties() overlays 'cfg:section.key=val' CLI args (highest precedence)",
      "6. expandConfig() resolves ${VAR}/$__env{VAR}/$__file{path} references in all remaining values",
      "7. parseINIFile() dispatches to ~30 readXxx functions; each reads its section via cfg.Raw.Section() or SectionWithEnvOverrides(), applying per-key defaults via MustString/MustBool/MustInt",
      "8. ProvideProvider(cfg) wraps cfg in OSSImpl and registers it as hs.SettingsProvider",
      "9. GET /api/admin/settings → AdminGetSettings() → hs.SettingsProvider.Current()",
      "10. OSSImpl.Current() iterates cfg.Raw sections/keys, calls RedactedValue(EnvKey(section,key), key.Value()) for every key → SettingsBag with masked values",
      "11. getAuthorizedSettings() filters the SettingsBag by RBAC (settings:read permission, scoped to settings:*, settings:<section>:*, or settings:<section>:<key>)",
      "12. response.JSON(200, authorizedBag) serialises the filtered, masked bag as the HTTP response"
    ]
  }
